On October 6, 2017, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation declaring it German-American Day. The proclamation recognizes the important contributions of German immigrants and their descendants to the United States. It highlights notable German-Americans in various fields such as business, finance, military, arts, and engineering. The proclamation also emphasizes the close relationship between the United States and Germany and the importance of a strong partnership. President Trump calls upon all Americans to celebrate German-American achievements and contributions to the nation.